snippet.textDisplay: While what's said in the theory is true, when watching the movies and stuff I always kinda saw it as Dory becoming the main female in the relationship, even if not sexually. So would a Clownfish still transition if another female was introduced into the group before the transition completed or whatever? I'm not sure if studies have been done on that or if they have I haven't been able to find the results of it. Alternatively, Finding Nemo 3 could have them meet another group of Clownfish with a female in that group and join in with them, Marlin potentially dies and Nemo becomes the main male of the new group or whatever. Since Nemo would be "of age" at that point they could play it as one of those classic tropes of a parent wanting their kid to have a mate and give them grandkids and Nemo being an angsty teenager and stuff. Keep it relevant to both kids and adults, Disney is really good at that.

snippet.textDisplay:
question: how small are schools of clown fish in real life? a school of 2-3 as we see in the first movie makes me far more willing to accept the theory that marlin and nemo are outcasts, or more specifically, adopting the more human trait of independence as a familial unit. Who's to say marlin is the alpha male, anyway? we are talking about disney, a company not known for showing the more intimate parts of family creation, so is it not also possible that marlin is only acting as the guard of the adolescent fish?


i will admit that my aversion to this theory mostly comes from the idea of forced gender transformation on a character the audience is supposed to be rooting for, and the fact that it has not been spelled out as anything the characters have prior knowledge of. The fish in the movie were given higher intelligence for the purpose of delivering the story to a wider audience (such as their ability to speak English and adopt human personality tendencies), so you would think marlin would know the change is coming and warn "nemo" (more accurately: indirectly to the audience), and that is without even getting into the argument of "true respectful love would allow the separation for mental health and not even attempt to Find Nemo".
